- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a coinductive technique to check program equivalence in a functional language, which is a topic closely related to logic.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the applicative bisimulation technique in the context of a lambda calculus extended with probabilistic and quantum features, which is a topic related to programming languages.
- cs.TL (Theoretical Computer Science) is another likely category as the paper presents theoretical results on the soundness of the obtained notions of bisimilarity.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the formal verification of program equivalence using bisimulation.
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with quantum data, which is an emerging technology in computer science.
